BARD OVERVIEW

Bards are flexible performers, fighters, scouts, social meddlers, and support
specialists. They are not built around one perfect damage button. They are built
around keeping momentum alive and turning a room's emotional state in their
favor.

Core ideas:

  Performance
    Your Bard momentum meter. Songs build it, especially when you vary song
    forms. Charisma improves how quickly this momentum builds. Some stronger
    powers require or spend it.

  Song fields
    Many newer Bard songs create a field that follows the Bard, pulses while it
    lasts, and affects allies or enemies nearby. Charisma increases song force
    and helps fields linger longer.

  Song forms
    Rhythm, Melody, Harmony, Dissonance, Crescendo, and Finale each do different
    jobs. Chaining forms can reveal hidden harmonies.

  Instruments
    Your lute works anywhere, but alternate instruments can change songs, unlock
    certain songs, and pair with archetypes.

  Archetypes
    At guild level 10, specialize lets you choose a deeper style such as War
    Conductor, Shadow Minstrel, Skald, Virtuoso, or Doom Singer.

  Social tools
    Bards can perform, spread fame or defamation, study emotional resonance,
    communicate well, and use lore-oriented abilities to understand the world.

Attributes:

  Charisma is the Bard's signature attribute and now directly influences nearly
  every major Bard performance: song strength, song duration, Performance gain,
  hidden harmony reward, morale pressure, Finale impact, and several older
  Bard support powers. Agility and intelligence also fit the guild well.
  Strength, constitution, and wisdom are useful, but the guild is not meant to
  be a simple brute-force path.

Armor and weapons:

  Bards can fight and use a wide range of equipment, but heavy equipment can
  work against some Bardic techniques. If a song or subtle ability seems poor,
  check your gear, instrument, Performance, and current song field.

